%% Model Registry Operator - Data Flow Diagram
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6

sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant Route as OpenShift Route<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant Proxy as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant K8sAPI as K8s API Server<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant MR as model-registry REST<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant DB as PostgreSQL/MySQL<br/>5432/TCP or 3306/TCP

    Note over Client,DB: Flow 1: Model Registry REST API Request (Authenticated)

    Client->>Route: HTTPS/443 Request
    Route->>Proxy: HTTPS/8443 (reencrypt TLS)
    Proxy->>K8sAPI: TokenReview + SubjectAccessReview<br/>HTTPS/6443, SA token
    K8sAPI-->>Proxy: Auth Result (allow/deny)
    Proxy->>MR: HTTP/8080 (localhost, no auth)
    MR->>DB: Query/Update<br/>5432/TCP PostgreSQL<br/>Username/Password auth
    DB-->>MR: Query Result
    MR-->>Proxy: Response
    Proxy-->>Route: HTTPS Response
    Route-->>Client: HTTPS Response

    Note over Client,DB: Flow 2: ModelRegistry CR Reconciliation

    participant Operator as MR Operator<br/>Controller

    K8sAPI->>Operator: Watch Event (ModelRegistry CR)<br/>HTTPS/TLS, SA token
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create/Update Resources<br/>(Deployment, Service, Route, RBAC)<br/>HTTPS/6443, SA token
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Read OpenShift Ingress config<br/>(cluster domain for Routes)<br/>HTTPS/6443, SA token

    Note over Client,DB: Flow 3: Model Catalog Data Population

    participant CatInit as Init Container<br/>(catalog-data-init)
    participant CatMR as Catalog Container<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant CatDB as Catalog PostgreSQL<br/>5432/TCP
    participant CatProxy as Catalog kube-rbac-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS

    CatInit->>CatInit: Write catalog data to EmptyDir
    CatMR->>CatDB: Connect and populate<br/>5432/TCP PostgreSQL<br/>Username/Password from secret
    Client->>CatProxy: HTTPS/8443 Catalog Request
    CatProxy->>K8sAPI: SubjectAccessReview<br/>HTTPS/6443
    K8sAPI-->>CatProxy: Auth Result
    CatProxy->>CatMR: HTTP/8080 (localhost)
    CatMR-->>CatProxy: Catalog Response
    CatProxy-->>Client: HTTPS Response
